channel.description: Well i have 3 modems connected to 1 computer but on my other computer(the 1 im on right now) i only have the linksys connected to it when i do ipconfig i get 192.162.1.199 (not my ip but u no wat i mean) then when i go on no-ip.org it says Logged in as: simdog.simeon@g..... IP: 75.168.223 wat ip should i use for my no-ip thing im using the 192.162.1.199 it works to get me on and my other computer on and when i do ip config on other computer i get 192.162.1.198 and with the ipchicken i get 75.168.223 so they both same ip or somtin and wat ip should i use in my no-ip cause with my linksys router i only get to change the last numbers and it doesnt start with 75 ...... ty for help

item.title: Help w/ Linksys portforwarding
item.dc:creator: @Buddy_budster Buddy_budster
item.description:
@Buddy_budster wrote:

Well 75.168.223 is you ip adress. 192.162.1.198 is what you would put in to edit you portforward (defult gateway) options. so for this what i belive you should do would be to use 75.168.223 as your no-ip and edit your portforward option with your other one.

for exabmple my ip i use with no-ip is 99.248.188.78 but my defult gate way is 99.248.188.78. and my portforward edit is 192.168.0.1. so its exact same as everyon has.

hope it help,
Buddy

P.S im not very good at explaining hope you understand
